I am not the biggest fan of my crate but will sleep in there during the nighttime. I am almost completely potty trained and as long as you take me out every few hours I won't have any accidents. I am very curious of other people and dogs when I go outside and love to sniff around in the grass. I typically have a lot of energy but my foster parents take me on nice long walks to tire me out.

I hope I can meet my new family soon!

Crew is a male Collie/Spaniel Mix born around 7/10/2018 and currently weighs 36lbs.

animal.description:
Boomer was found by a good Samaritan on Christmas Eve. He was found huddled next to a fence and injured. After a visit to vet, it was determined that he had either been hit by a car or thrown from a car. He had a fractured back leg, but it is aligned and healing well. He has a bit of a limp right now, but is expected to make a complete recovery. Boomer's injury hasn't slowed him down a bit though! You won't find a happier friendlier boy

Boomer is a wonderful dog. He is house trained, can sit and use doggy door. He is not happy being crated, but at his foster home does well without being crated. He wants to be a lap dog and loves to receive and give affection.

Boomer would do well with an active family who is home or with another active dog. He loves to take walks, but since he is still recuperating, has not been able to exercise as much as normal. He would do great with children and loves car rides. Boomer is a great, loving dog who will make a great addition to a family. If you'd like to meet Boomer, please fill out a no-obligation application at www.tmhpr.com/adopt. Boomer's estimated birthdate is 6/16/19.
Please visit our website at tmhpr.com for more information. If you are interested in meeting one of our pets, please fill out the on-line adoption application on our website.

Dogs (all prices include sales tax)

Puppies (under 12 months): $325

Dogs (over 12 months) $270

Large-Breed Dogs (over 75 lbs) $300

Cats (all prices include sales tax

Kittens (under 12 months) $165

Cats (over 12 months) $135

Rescued Declawed Cats* $160

* TMHPR does not endorse the declawing of cats

Safe pet home visits & vet checks are required. For this reason, we only adopt locally - in the Dallas area. For more information about our rescue organization and our available pets, please visit tmhpr.com.

animal.description: Derrick is an energetic young dude just waiting for a family that is just as excited as he is to teach him how to tame his energy! Derrick is a go, go, go kind of guy and has the energy to prove it! Derrick will be the perfect running or adventure buddy! He is still working on proper manners when greeting and playing with people, but he loves a good treat and is very food motivated. Derrick is a resource guarder and does not like to share high value treats and toys, but he is great at trading! Toys are one of Derrick's favorite things balls, ropes, and squeaky toys he loves them all! He will be a great companion and his antics will always put a smile on your face! Due to Derrick's resource guarding, he is looking for a home without small children. Derrick is an active boy with specific needs, which makes him one of our last-to-be-adopted pets, affectionately known as our Unfurgettable Friends! animal.description: Meet Pancake!  So handsome!   We are really enjoying this fur baby!!! Pancake ended up at a shelter and came in as a stray.  He is a young guy at probably about a year old or maybe a little yes and weighs about 38 pounds so not a huge dog. Pancake (Name given at the shelter) is an energetic boy that would love an energetic outlet.  He needs an avenue to burn some energy like going to a dog park a few times a week.  But...he really is quite calm in a home setting which is surprising with his young age. Also, he is smart and learns routines quickly. He learned sit very quickly and picks up routines quickly.  One of Pancakes' best qualities is that he loves other animals so he would be a good dog park dog for sure. He is a little shy with humans so we are working on that with him and he is making a lot of progress. After a 24 hour period he is your best friend.   Even though he is great with other animals, we think he would be best suited for a home without other animals so that he will bond with his humans as he tends to bond with other dogs.  He is not aggressive at all with other animals but he does get super HAPPY around them and his energy level goes way up.  We think Pancake is going to make a great dog for someone with some love and patience. He just needs some basic manners and structure in his life which a person with a rescue heart can provide!  If you would like an adoption application, email storkwoods@comcast.net.  This is how we begin each potential adoption. We are an all volunteer based rescue trying to save as many as we can!

YHT does not adopt dogs out of state 
Little Tres, a black beauty, born roughly end of September, was a lucky girl.  She was stray, saved by our trapping team while on the reservation helping to secure another litter of pups, when she was nearly hit by oncoming cars. 
This girl has personality plus, and is simply adorable. We are not sure of her breed(s) possibly spaniel or retriever and that mysterious rescue gene. She has sparkly eyes, constant curiosity and is full of that puppy playful spirit. She loves to play fetch and tug of war. Tres loves water and anything that moves captures her attention.  She lies on her back to rest and holds her toys between her paws like a cat.  She is smart and learns quickly.  She sleeps quietly in her kennel at night. She knows sit, down, off (very hard for her to remember that so far), leave it (we are working on that one) and has just started her leash training.  Her food preferences so far are “anything”.
 Tres would love a dog buddy to play with, a secure attached fence yard, and a human with some time at home during the day to further her training and socializing.  Please contact 4lvdch@bullerinetworks.net to fill out a pre-adopt form so that you can meet this cutie.

animal.description:
Hi I’m Maverick! 
Not the one from the movie “Top Gun“, but I do have a need for speed! Of course that’s only outdoors. I love flying across the yard and lauding my flying skills and locking in on my target. I’m excited for takeoff but will “Sit and wait”. Once my guidance radar locks in I’ll retrieve my target and return it with a perfect landing, awaiting take off again. 

I excel at learning, practicing my agility, being a part of a squadron that’ll support my desire for being the best I can be. I can chill with the best of them inside & yet excel outside. With a bit of time & training i could be a competitive dog athlete - everything from agility, to flyball, even frisbee competitions could be possibilities.

As I stated earlier I love to chill with my squadron. I love to be told I’m the best, inverted for petting, spoiled with treats and knowing “You’ve got that lovin’ feeling” for me.

Now for my personal info. I’m a 3 yr old, 55 lb. Lab/Pointer and who knows what else is in the mix!  I’m not sure of my DNA but I know I’m HANDSOME! 

I’m house-trained, and when it’s time to go out I do well on a leash. No chewing except on my bones and toys. I don’t get on the furniture unless asked to and I also mind my manners. I don’t use a crate and I sleep on my doggie bed at night. I’m good with people of all ages, good with dogs but cats unknown.

Could you be my new squadron? Are you willing to help me be the best I can be, as I love you unconditionally?

Our standard adoption fee is $375 cash or check and $385 credit card ($10 processing fee). .  It includes spay/neuter when age appropriate at our participating vets, age appropriate core vaccinations, fecal testing, deworming, flea and tick preventative,1st vet visit at one of our participating vets, and micro-chipping. 


We must have an application, conduct a phone interview, and meet your entire family to approve an adoption. Please email adopt@safehavendogsIL.org for an application or additional details.

Please note that the breeds and sizes posted in this biography are educated best guesses and are not guaranteed.

Please consider becoming a foster home while you search for your new best friend. We need foster homes - pounds are overflowing with puppies and adult dogs that are at-risk and need help. We can only rescue as many as we have foster home commitments. Fostering is a rewarding experience for your family.

animal.description:
Charlie is a Puppy Pals alum and he is now looking for a new home; an incredibly difficult decision by his mom of almost six years. He is a small super mutt who is 9 years old. He’s still a bit active and his favorite activities are playing fetch, running around in the backyard, and chasing the cat at his foster home. As much as he loves his activities, he’s a total cuddle bug. Charlie loves to sit on his foster mom’s lap or curled up with the resident senior dog. They patrol the neighborhood together from the window. He has gotten along fine with the other dogs who are in his foster house.

Charlie loves his crate and has no problem with going in there to lay down when no one is home. He will also alert his foster mom when he needs to go outside. Charlie would be suitable for a home with dogs, but would also be perfectly happy as a single companion lap dog.

Charlie is being fostered in Kettering by Whitney.

Contact this foster home at whitney.tobias@gmail.com

To Adopt This Pup:

Go to PPR's Applications Page at www.puppypalsrescue.com and apply!

Please email the foster home to let them know you have applied, as sometimes forms seem to get lost in cyberspace.

animal.description:
Barnes is a cool dog with a sad backstory. His owner turned him over to animal control with a note on the surrender saying "I do not want him anymore". They missed out-he is friendly, outgoing, and so so happy to be near his people. That makes sense, we guess, because the owner said he was an outside dog, so not sure how much time he spent with him. But Barnes holds no grudges against humans and loves everyone. When he first meets you, he is so excited that he does jump up to greet you so probably no young kids at this point until he knows how to properly sit and greet calmly. He's working on it. He has sit down pat for his dinner, that is for sure. He likes his food :) Barnes is a very high energy dog, though, and needs a very active home that will exercise him regularly and knows how to tire out a Siberian.
Barnes is good with other dogs. He is still a young active dog so he'd probably be a bit too much for a sedate or senior dog. But he likes to play with other dogs. We are looking for an active home for him with someone who is willing to put in some basic training to make him the perfect house dog. He will be a perfect boy in no time.

animal.description:
If napping were an Olympic sport, Everhart would surely win the Gold. He's not only an award winning cuddler, this eight month old, sweater-wearing stud muffin is also very smart and curious and is so adorable that even cat-people stop to gush over him.

Everhart loves everyone that he meets and quickly makes himself comfortable wherever he goes. He weighs about 45lbs, loves to play with other dogs, is an A+ travel passenger and is quickly learning that all of the cool dogs are housetrained.

When he isn't napping or playing with his dog friends he enjoys belly rubs, spending more time smelling things than actually walking during his daily walks around the neighborhood, throwing his toys in the air and catching them, prancing around while incessantly squeaking his toy after a successful catch and, well, probably deciding when he'll take his next nap.

If you are interested in adopting Everhart please submit an inquiry directly with Greater Charlotte SPCA by visiting charlottespca.org/adopt.

***Because our rescue is composed entirely of volunteers and we require a home check for each of our adoptable pets prior to them going to their new homes, local applications will take precedence. We will accept out of town applications, but any family further than 60 miles from Charlotte is responsible for finding a representative of a rescue local to them that is willing to perform the home check. All out of town applicants will also have to be willing to drive to Charlotte to meet/pick up the pet as soon as the application is approved.***

Housebroken: Yes
Crate trained: Working on it! Takes some time to settle but overall doing well with his crate training
Dog sociability: Reportedly dog-friendly from transferring shelter. Hasn't had too much interaction with dogs in current foster home.
Cat sociability: Unknown
Kids: Not a match - he can startle easily and does best with adults.

Swipe right if you're looking for a handsome gentleman with eyes that will make you melt! Winston is a loving, gentle, and loyal companion who is seeking his forever home to enjoy endless hugs and kisses. Winston is a polite, house trained, and relaxed dog who will always make you feel loved as he is most comfortable snuggled up next to you. When he's not chewing on his bone, Winston loves to play ball and won't object if you sneak him an extra treat after a long walk or nap. Winston has endless love to give and promises to make you feel all the warm and fuzzies inside every time you see him! 

Winston's adoption fee is 300. He is neutered, up to date on core vaccines, microchipped and heartworm negative.

Jarret is living in a foster home. Submit an application from our website and then make an appointment to meet him.

Jarret is not eligible for foster and will be a straight adoption.

Age: ~3 years 
Weight: ~58lbs
Housebroken: Yes
Crate trained: Working on it! Takes time to settle (10-30 minutes) and will benefit from continued training for this
Dog sociability: Friendly! Lives with dogs in his foster home and has been doing well. He is playful and can be a rough & tumble type of player, so does best with equally playful/tolerant dogs. On walks, he may pull towards dogs to meet them
Cat sociability: Unknown
Kids: Unknown, but can be sensitive to noise so likely best with older kiddos.
Ideal home: Jarret is a sweet, active pup looking for a home that can work on training! He has some energy to burn and will do great in a home where he can exhaust his energy in positive ways. He would likely love a dog pal that can wrestle with him, or access to doggy daycare. He can be sensitive to apartment sounds, so he isn't a match for a large apartment building/noisy building and would prefer to not live in an elevator building.

Jarrett is a playful boy with a zest for life! He loves his people, he loves his dog friends, he loves walks, he loves naps, he just loves to love! Jarrett is easily excited but fortunately settles down easily as well- He's the perfect Sunday morning hike partner followed by Sunday afternoon nap partner. Jarrett doesn't know his own size and is working on his manners/basic training but with just how much he loves people we believe training him to be a very well-behaved best friend will be not only doable but a ton of fun! He's fully potty trained and sleeps 8 hours in his crate without issue. Jarrett is currently living in a foster home with 2 dogs and has been doing well.

Jarret's adoption fee is 300. He is neutered, up to date on core vaccines, microchipped and heartworm negative. He will require booster vaccines at the adopter's expense.

animal.description:
***PLEASE READ ENTIRE BIO & ADOPTION CRITERIA BEFORE CONTACTING ODR OR APPLYING FOR ADOPTION, THANKS!***


MEET Willie Mays -

Willie Mays is a 5.5 year old neutered dachshund. He's 12.5 lbs, red smooth, very active boy! Doxie saavy and stay at home only please apply. No other dogs, kids or cats, he must be the one and only. He has some nipping history with kids and other dogs. He adores walks,  car rides, snuggling, and burrowing under blankets. He loves his squeeker toys, but hedgehogs are his favorite. NO STEPS/STAIRS. He had a mild case of IVDD, doing great now. He is a great watchdog, but a little barky. He is on doggie xanax for some anxiety. This is one cute over the top little guy! Just needs a little patience and love. If you think you would be a good fit please fill out an application today!

Willie Mays will do best in a family with a stay at home parent (work from home or retired) and only older children (over age 12), who are familiar with the special needs of Dachshunds.

Like all Dachshunds, Willie Mays is high energy and enjoys playing and warming his little bones in the sunshine, so along with regular walks around his neighborhood, Willie Mays needs a secure fenced yard to run around and explore safely. While small in stature, doxies are big on personality and don't generally do well in apartments, with all of the noises and traffic that come with multiple dwellings in a confined space.  To best set up our doxies and their new families for success, ODR, Inc., adopt to families who live in single family homes with secure fenced yards.

OUR CRITERIA (aka The Fine Print):

Based on 30 years of experience with rescue doxies, we have pretty strict criteria. Do you work from home/stay at home/work part time?  Have a securely fenced yard? We do not place same gender dogs in a home unless they were raised together, and children need to be 12 or older (some exceptions IF the dog is a puppy or the child has been raised with a doxie). We prefer non smokers and a home with no other small animals (ferrets, hamsters, etc). Cats are on a case by case basis depending on the dog. Remember, these are rescues; many were surrendered because of these issues. 

WHAT YOU GET IN RETURN WITH YOUR LITTLE RESCUE:

All our dogs are fully vetted, including spay/neuter, rabies, DHPP, Bordetella, Pyrantyl, nails trimmed, and dental when needed. They'll come with a basket of goodies, food, toys and a custom made harness. The adoption fee is $495, sorry no exceptions, as this covers the cost to rescue them, vet them and take care of them while in our rescue. It also helps towards the care of other doxies that come with huge vet or dental bills or need extensive behavioral training.

Can you give Willie Mays a happy, carefree life again? If interested, please complete the adoption questionnaire at www.odr-inc.org and email it to: jrangan@comcast.net 
The adoption committee will attempt to be in contact with you within 48-72 hours. Please be patient as we are solely volunteer run.

PLEASE DO NOT ASK ABOUT AVAILABILITY OR EMAIL THROUGH PETFINDER or ADOPT-A-PET - WE CANNOT RESPOND - READ THE PROCESS BELOW.

If you're interested in any of our wonderful dogs, you must FIRST fill out an Adoption Application at our website listed below. Once we receive it, we'll forward it to the foster family for follow up. We are 100% foster based, so we don't have a facility. Review the process FAQ at our website.

Adoption applications can be found here: http://labrescuefresno.org/available-labs/adoption-application/

Adoption Fees Adult Dog (10 mos. - 7 years): $250.00 Puppy (9 mos. and under): $350.00 Senior (8 yrs. and up)/Special Needs Dog: $100.00

Buddy, Black Male mix, 5 year old, 90 lbs.
Howdy Lab lovers! My name is Buddy - seriously, that's what my owner named me. If you have something more original in mind, I'm open to changing my name. My pre-rescue life is a bit of a mystery. All I can tell you is that one day some people in uniforms came and separated me from my owner and took me to the Animal Shelter. It was very noisy there and I didn't like it at all. But after a couple of weeks, one of the wonderful people from the Defenders of Dogs picked me up and took me to her house. I'd be plenty happy to stay here forever, but she explained to me that it has to be temporary so she can rescue another pup like me and that she will find me the very best forever home. Though I really do love living with my foster family, I also really want more dogs like me to get their forever families too, so let's do this! My heart is open and full of love to give to my forever family!
At my foster home, I have three dog siblings and a cat. I get along with them all. I've met a few new people, including one really little person - like so little that I'm taller than she is! I accidentally knocked her down in my excitement to meet all the new people, but she just laughed, so we're all good.
You may notice from my glamour shots that I have a bit of white on my face, ears and feet. The people at the animal shelter estimated my age at 4-5 years. My foster mom thinks some of that white hair may be whatever breed(s) I am mixed with or some of us are just blessed with premature grey hair - hey I think it looks quite distinguished! I do like to play like a younger pup and I am very strong. Besides playing with my foster brother, my favorite thing to do is to snooze on the sofa with my foster mom. By the way, for those glamour shots, I had to get a bath, and I don't like water at all! Yuck! Bleh! Pooey!
Buddy is house-trained, crate-trained, he knows "sit", and is very affectionate and loving. He is a strong athletic guy and needs to work on his leash manners, so Buddy will do best with a family that is committed to taking training classes together to master proper leash skills and ensure a lifetime of good behavior. Buddy is quite an energetic fella for his age and will need a family who is willing and able to exercise him daily.
Looking for a best friend? If you want to make Buddy a member of your family forever, please apply today at www.labrescuefresno.org.

If you are interested in adopting through Labrador Retriever Rescue of Fresno, you must first fill out an Adoption Application located at our website www.LabRescueFresno.org All dogs are spayed/neutered, up to date on age appropriate vaccines including rabies; flea/tick topical drops, heartworm tested and microchipped. Thank you for opting to adopt!!

animal.description:
Lulu is an adorable girl that we pulled from a local kill shelter. She is about 8 months old and weighs only 11 pounds. This pup has a gorgeous, soft black coat with just a tiny bit of white stripe on her chest. Lulu is perfectly crate trained and sleeps on a very nice plush dog bed. In the short time we have had her, she has never had an accident so it is possible she may already be house-trained. Unfortunately we are not able to know for sure. Friendly & sweet, Lulu is also a bit timid and is still getting used to our place as well as walking on a leash. Lulu loves everyone she meets and is more than happy to snuggle in your lap. She is used to being crated at night and playing in a safe, fenced yard during the day with other foster pups the same size. Lulu seems fine with other dogs but would be best placed in a home without cats. Lulu is now healthy, fully vetted and ready for her forever home. Her wish list consists of an inside forever home with a big fenced yard for playtime, a home with lots of toys and another doggy friend for play time and pet parents who understand the time commitment that a new dog requires. Adopters who are retired or work-from-home parents are ideal as they have the time to spend with the pet. Adopters committed to doing a 6 week basic obedience class to ensure Lulu's successful transition into a new home environment would also a plus (and to ensure the new puppy parent's education level). If you think you have the perfect home for Lulu, contact us at info.caresga@gmail.com for an adoption application. We adopt up north and all over so please ask for details. $400 adoption fee and a vet reference is required to ensure a great home (this means you have had a pet so we can call to verify their level of care). Eligibility for adoption means your current or past pets are spayed/neutered, up to date on vaccines and on monthly heartworm and flea prevention. Please be aware that we do not allow shock collars (ie underground fences) or "pens" as an alternative for a fenced yard.

We do our best to place our rescue pets in the very best homes. Please be aware that we have an application which also includes required vet records showing your existing pets are current on preventative medical care. Puppy adopters please take note that we generally try to place our puppies into homes where at least one parent is retired/stay at home/works from home to ensure the puppy gets enough attention and training (puppies cannot hold it all day in a crate) so please have a plan ready when contacting us. For safety reasons, we try not to place small dogs or puppies in families with children under 5 (there may be exceptions depending on situation).

Typical adoption fees for puppies are $350, juvenile dogs $300, adults dogs are $250, senior dogs are $150. Some pets, smaller dogs for example, may have a higher than normal adoption fee but we will alert you if there is a variance. Dogs rescued from China always have a higher adoption fee. Adoption fees help our group offset PART of the cost of rescuing, rehabilitating, and getting the pet healthy so they can go on to find a loving home with someone willing to give them a second chance at life. This amount includes each animal being current on age appropriate vaccinations including DHPPL, bordetella, influenza, rabies, and boosters when appropriate. De-wormed for any internal parasites (round worms, hook worms, tape worms and whipworms) with Drontal Plus, 4DX tested heart-worm negative (if positive, they are treated), tested negative for tick borne diseases, spayed/neutered, implanted with a micro-chip and have been examined by a veterinarian to certify that they are healthy. Any other known health issues are treated as well prior to adoption (examples: UTI, broken bones, contagious infections, dental cleanings, etc). All animals are also on a regime of flea and heartworm medication every month. Lifetime registration for the micro-chip is included in each adoption fee. In addition, each adopter will go home with a fitted collar, tags, a bag of dog food the pet has been on, copies of all vet history, and an adoption kit filled with valuable information and coupons as well as other various treats or toys as promotions become available. All puppy adoptions include two puppy training books, the Puppy Primer & Way To Go by Patricia McConnell, and all adult adoptions go home with Love Has No Age Limit by Patricia McConnell to help ensure a smooth transition for your new family member.

We ask that you consider an additional donation on top of this pet's adoption fee. This money will go directly into our Adoption Fund to be used exclusively for rescuing and caring for other pets in need. Many pets we take in have very high vet bills to get them healthy and adoptable for the public - much higher than their adoption fees. We receive no government funding and rely solely on donations from our community and caring adopters to continue our rescue efforts!

animal.description:
Meet Heidi! She is an adorable 2 years old Pit mix. Heidi is very sweet, housebroken, crate trained, spayed and up/to-date on vaccinations. She is all about the cuddles and play time.  
Heidi is exceedingly smart and responds to training quickly especially when there are treats involved. She is absolutely food motivated and eager to please. Heidi loves long walks that last upwards of 45-minutes but is just as happy with 2-3 shorter walks (roughly around the block) throughout the day.  She has been crate trained but still requires a little encouragement when it's time for bed. Heidi is a vocal dog who loves to be outside chasing squirrels and birds and rodents and when she is not outside she can usually be found staring out of the window watching the world outside.  She loves to play with furry toys but rarely destroys them! Loves deer antlers and peanut butter shoved inside larger bones. 
If you're a runner or hiker you are missing out if you pass up the opportunity to adopt this dog. Please consider making her part of your family. She will be forever grateful. 

Adoption Process: Please visit http://heavenlypawsmi.com/adoptions and fill out an Adoption Questionnaire.

Adoption Costs: There is a $175.00 adoption fee to support the care and well being of all of our adoptable pets. Heavenly Paws of Michigan is a strong supporter of spay and neutering. Thank you for your interest in saving a shelter dog.

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Please contact Mary (MHSAbbyRescue@gmail.com) for more information about this pet.Cinnamon's adoption donation is $325 and she is being fostered in Central Ohio. She has been spayed, microchipped, received her rabies, distemper/parvo, bivalent canine influenza, and bordetella vaccines, tested negative for heartworms and started on prevention, as well as flea prevention. Cinnamon has also had a dental cleaning.
She will require a home with a companion dog of similar size and a secure, physically fenced yard.

Cinnamon is a a sweet girl who was surrendered to our rescue from a commercial breeder. Cinnamon is an appproximately 8-9 year old Yorkie or Silky mix. She is learning how to be a dog and had made significant progress in rescue. Cinnamon does well on housetraining if kept on a schedule. Just like most mill dogs, she is learning how to be a dog and discovering new things all the time, but she is shy and does things on her schedule. She loves other dogs and definitely looks to them for guidance. She will need a patient, experienced adopter who will give her the time to decompress and settle into her new home.
Cinnamon will require a home with a companion dog of similar size and a secure, physically fenced yard.
PLEASE NOTE: If you are viewing this biography on a website other than the Ohio Fuzzy Pawz website, not all information transfers to partner websites in some instances. If you go to the individual webpage of our dogs, you will be able to get more information each dog.

Visual breed identification in dogs can be unreliable so, in many cases, we are only guessing at the predominant breed or breed mix. We get to know each dog as an individual and will do our best to describe each of our dogs based on personality, not by breed label.

Our Adoption Process

The adoption process has several steps involved.

Please review prior to submitting an application.
Our adoption process is detailed here:

http://www.ohiofuzzypawz.com/info/adoption

Our volunteers work very diligently to process each application and we try to ensure that we are making the best match possible for each dog. We do not schedule meetings with dogs until an application has been approved. It can take up to a few weeks to process an application or as little time as a few days, from the time you submit an application, please be prepared to adopt as we cannot hold dogs.

Special Requirements

Some dogs may have special requirements (for example, medications, a fence) -- if you apply for a dog, please be sure to read over the biography completely to see if there are any special needs and if you're home would be suitable. If we indicate on the dog's biography that a fence is required, this means your home must have a physical fence. Other dogs may require a "strong vet reference" which indicates that we are looking for a home that has a documented history of veterinary care with previous pets.

The first step in our process is to submit an online adoption application at www.ohiofuzzypawz.com/forms. The application MUST include the personal references and veterinary, grooming, and landlord references (if applicable) and their respective contact information. If you do not include the references and the contact information, your application will be delayed as it CANNOT be processed. Once the references have been successfully completed, a home visit is then scheduled when a rescue representative can meet all members of the family or residents of the home.
No application is approved prior to the home visit being done.
At that point, the Directors will discuss any and all applications on a foster dog and make a selection--in many cases, there are multiple applications for each dog, so please be understanding that our only priority is the successful placement of each of our foster dogs.

Out of State Adoptions

We do adopt out of state to outstanding applicants, however, our process requires a home visit, so out of state adoptions can take longer.
We do not ship our dogs, adopters should be prepared to pick up the dog in Central Ohio.

animal.description:
Please contact C.A.R.E. for more information about this pet. Wigglesworth American Staffordshire Terrier, Born in 2017, Neutered male Greetings! I'm an adorable, stout, muscular bundle of energy with perky ears and gorgeous brown eyes. I'll bet you are wondering how I got my name, aren't you? Well, it's because I wiggle all over non-stop when I meet new friends. I just get so darn excited that I can't help it. My favorite thing is to be close to people. Cuddling, belly rubs, and pets? Yes, please! Besides affection, I also enjoy playing with toys, but sometimes I don't like to share. I want them all for myself. The volunteers call me 'Houdini' because I have mastered opening the doors at the shelter, so you'll need to do some puppy proofing at home. I used to be a stray, so I'm a little needy and fearful, and I bark due to separation anxiety. It's only because I want to be with my special person, an experienced dog owner who will go slowly with me and teach me not to be so fearful of things. Objects that you find normal scare me sometimes, and I need time to get used to them, build my trust, and show me the world is a good place. You won't regret it, and I'll be your friend for life. Don't tell anyone, but I'm wiggling just thinking about meeting you!
Adoption Information: Size: Medium/weighs 45 pounds Children: No Dogs: No Cats: No Adoption fee: $300 This dog is neutered, microchipped and has had a full veterinary checkup and vaccines.
If you are interested in more information or would like to meet this dog, please fill out our online adoption survey: carenorthshore.org/dog-adoption-survey

animal.description:
ADOPT ME ONLINE: https://ophrescue.org/dogs/10140

Hi! My name is Rasinets and Im part of the Candy transport. I am a super sweet girl who knows all of my commands. I listen like a good girl . I want to make you proud. 
Im guessed to be a Lab/Staffordshire mix and estimated to be about 1.5 years old. I currently weigh about 65lbs. 
 I am crate trained and low maintenance at my foster home, Ive learned potty training while in foster care.
One of my favorite activities is running around in the backyard with my foster brothers And sisters and also getting belly scratches. I am a snuggler! My foster mom says I give the best snuggles. you should know that I have serious hops! Im looking for a forever home with a fenced backyard that is high enough ( more then 5 ft) that I cant jump over it. 
I really enjoy car rides and am good on my leash when we go on walks. I play great with all dogs male female . I love playing fetch with my ball and playing with all toys. Im perfectly happy to hang out at home with you and get scratches and rubs. Im protective of my home and need to be introduced to guests. 
I can be a little bit shy when you first meet me. Give me a little time to warm up, and we will be a great match!
Apply today! 
To adopt this dog, or any OPH dog, fill out the simple online application at https://ophrescue.org 
Operation Paws for Homes, Inc. (OPH) rescues dogs of all breeds and ages from high-kill shelters in NC, VA, MD, and SC, reducing the numbers being euthanized. With limited resources, the shelters are forced to put down 50-90% of the animals that come in the front door. OPH provides pet adoption services to families located in VA, DC, MD, PA and neighboring states. OPH is a 501(c)(3) organization and is 100% donor funded. OPH does not operate a shelter or have a physical location. We rely on foster families who open their homes to give love and attention to each dog before finding a forever home.

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Please contact APe for more information about this pet.Thanks for your interest in a pet from A.R.F.! If you see a pet here, they are still available for adoption and you should apply through our adoption application on our website at https://www.arf-il.org/adopt/application/
Hi my name is Brewer! My previous family said my DNA test listed my primary breed as Boxer, but my ARF peeps think I look a bit like a Rhodesian Ridgeback mix too. Either way, I am a handsome boy if I do say so myself! My foster parents call me a gentle giant, because I am a big boy who weighs in at 80 pounds. I am about 4 years old, very sweet, and house-trained. I still love to run and play and would love a fenced in yard. I know a number of commands like "sit", "stay", "down", and "place". I don't use my bark often, but when I do, it is because I hear something scary and I need to protect you! After a long day of playing and exercise, I will cuddle up next to my humans on the couch. I do really well on walks and I can sleep nicely in my crate at night. I can get along with kids but I prefer that they are older and know how to give me my space. I would prefer to be the only animal because I am a bit of an "alpha" and might mount other dogs when I feel threatened. Overall, my foster parents love me! I am so excited for my forever home.

Brewer is micro-chipped, up to date on all vaccinations, housebroken and neutered. His new family will be required to complete a basic obedience course of their choosing.

Brewer's adoption fee is $300. A meeting will not be scheduled until you have an approved application, so if you're interested in adopting Brewer fill out an Online Application today!

Once your application has been approved, an ARF volunteer will contact you to arrange a meeting.

Thank you for considering a rescue pet from A.R.F.-Animal Rescue Foundation! We are
based in Wheaton, IL and conduct adoption events in the DuPage County area. If you are interested in adopting one of our pets, please submit an adoption application at https://www.arf-il.org/adopt/application/

Adoption appointments are scheduled based on the order of applications received, so submit your application early! Submitting an application does not commit you to any animal but does get you a head start with the adoption approval process. Due to a high volume of applications, we are often unable to respond to questions or schedule meetings until your application has been approved. More information about our adoption process can be found on our website here: https://www.arf-il.org/adopt/

As an all-volunteer, foster home-based organization, A.R.F. Animal Rescue Foundation does not have a facility where applicants can visit our animals. Please visit https://www.arf-il.org/events/ for a list of our upcoming adoption events.

Thank you for choosing to adopt, not shop!

animal.description:
Welcome Barry to Wags 2 Wishes! 
Barry is a spunky 1 yr old Chi Mix.
Barry around 17 lbs of fun! 

Barry is a sweet, energetic boy.
He loves to play with his fun loving foster siblings! And can't wait to find a home of his very own!
Even though Barry is almost 1 he is still very much a puppy so he’s still learning the ropes. He can be mouthy, chewy and rambunctious. So an owner with breed experience and patience will help Mr.Barry thrive.
Because he can be mouthy we looking for a home w +13 yrs or older.

He does well in a crate and should be in a crate when not supervised. 
He has done well with house training and wee pads but he still has the occasional accident so someone who can give him a regular routine with a good amount of play and exercise would suit him well. 
Barry would love a home with a doggy playmate. He does best with female  dogs his size or bigger with the same spunky energy level.

 In true Chihuahua nature Barry is cautious of strangers and would need a slow introduction. 

Are you ready to fall in love and give Barry a home?
Apply and the adoption specialist will contact approved apps via email for meets!
Apply at w2wrescue.com 
Adoption fee $375

animal.description:
OUR ADOPTION APPLICATION AND PROCESS ARE AVAILABLE AT WWW.SOHODOGRESCUE.ORG AND OUR ADOPTION FEE IS $275.

Bailey is a young, frisky Border Collie who is ready for his forever home.  He is 1 year old, weighs 50 pounds and he has that classic black and white Border Collie coloring.  Bailey is housebroken, crate-trained, and while he knows his basic obedience commands the does not always choose to follow them!  He walks nicely on leash and he is a very good passenger in the car.
Bailey is a friendly guy who loves people.  Bailey is a high energy, medium-to-high Velcro boy who does have an “off switch” but a lot of play happens before then!  He loves to do almost anything active with his foster family – walking, hiking, playing ball, etc.  He also LOVES to play with other dogs.  He did not have a chance to play with other dogs before he was rescued, and he is still learning how to “talk dog”.  He sometimes misses their cues when other dogs have had enough of the game; he just loves to play and play and play.  Bailey also chases cats, squirrels, bugs, birds, anything that he spots while running in the yard!
The ideal home for Bailey is an active one, shared with a family who loves to play and is ready to add another frisky player to the “home team”.  A fenced yard and another young, playful dog are required, Border Collie experience is a plus, children over the age of 12 are welcome (he still jumps up on people and could easily knock over a small child!), and no cats please.  Bailey is a diamond in the rough; a fun-loving, happy, active guy with so much potential who needs a family that will continue his training and include him in the action.  We think he may enjoy dog sports that challenge his body and brain!  If you are ready for a Bailey in your life, apply today!  Bailey is fostered in Birchwood, TN.
